properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 29 at 3:21AM CST until January 29 at 11:00AM CST by NWS Bismarck ND
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Bismarck has issued a Dense Fog
Advisory, which is in effect until 11 AM CST /10 AM MST/ this
morning.

* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...Northwest, central, and southeast North Dakota.

* WHEN...Until 11 AM CST /10 AM MST/ Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Slippery travel conditions will be
possible as the fog deposits rime on roads, sidewalks and
bridges.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM CST /10 AM MST/ THIS MORNING
